The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, September 19, 2002 				 Reliance raises BSES stake
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								Mumbai, Sept. 18: The Reliance group has increased its stake in BSES Ltd to 40.29 per cent. In a notice to the National Stock Exchange here today, Reliance Power Ventures Ltd said the company/Reliance Industries Ltd, including persons acting in concert has purchased 32,64,720 shares amounting to 2.37 per cent and also sold 4,874 shares in the period between April 1 till yesterday.																								The shareholding after acquisition was 5,54,89,594 shares which amounts to 40.29 per cent, it said adding the shares were bought and sold through the market. As per the data available with the BSE, as on June 30, Reliance Industrial Investments amp; Holdings Ltd and Reliance Industries Ltd held 9.89 per cent and 1.13 per cent respectively in the power utility. Banks, financial institutions and insurance firms had 28.42 per cent stake in BSES followed by UTI at 8.66 per cent. 
